parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DPS system can cause the steering wheel to become firm or difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering and parking brake warning lights illuminate
the steering wheel becomes firm or difficult to turn
the vehicle is difficult to steer

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SE5 transmission can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, rapidly decelerate, or stall, which can lead to accidents, rear-end collisions, or loss of control.
symptoms: the transmission drops to neutral suddenly
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.
